coils_non_axisymmetric.documentation: Non axisymmetric active coils system (e.g. ELM control coils, error field correction coils, ...)

coils_non_axisymmetric.code.documentation: Generic decription of the code-specific parameters for the code that has produced this IDS

coils_non_axisymmetric.code.library.documentation: List of external libraries used by the code that has produced this IDS

coils_non_axisymmetric.code.library[:].p.documentation: List of the code specific parameters in XML format

coils_non_axisymmetric.code.output_flag.documentation: Output flag : 0 means the run is successful, other values mean some difficulty has been encountered, the exact meaning is then code specific. Negative values mean the result shall not be used.

coils_non_axisymmetric.code.parameters.documentation: List of the code specific parameters in XML format

coils_non_axisymmetric.coil[:].conductor.documentation: Set of conductors inside the coil. The structure can be used with size 1 for a simplified description as a single conductor. A conductor is composed of several elements, serially connected, i.e. transporting the same current.

The cross-section perpendicular to the conductor contour is described by a series of contour points, given by their relative position with respect to the start point of the first element. This cross-section is assumed constant for all elements.
Toroidal angles (relative to a reference point)
Index in the error_description list for "delta_phi"
Major radii (relative to a reference point)
Index in the error_description list for "delta_r"
Index in the error_description list for "delta_z"
Current in the conductor (positive when it flows from the first to the last element)
Index in the error_description list for "data"
Set of geometrical elements (line segments and/or arcs of a circle) describing the contour of the conductor centre
Position of the centre of the arc of a circle of every element (meaningful only if type/index = 2 or 3, fill with default/empty value otherwise)
Toroidal angle (oriented counter-clockwise when viewing from above)
Index in the error_description list for "phi"
Index in the error_description list for "r"
Index in the error_description list for "z"
Position of the end point of every element. Meaningful only if type/index = 1 or 2, fill with default/empty value otherwise
Toroidal angle (oriented counter-clockwise when viewing from above)
Index in the error_description list for "phi"
Index in the error_description list for "r"
Index in the error_description list for "z"

Position of an intermediate point along the arc of circle, for every element, providing the orientation of the element (must define with the corresponding start point an aperture angle strictly inferior to PI). Meaningful only if type/index = 2, fill with default/empty value otherwise
Toroidal angle (oriented counter-clockwise when viewing from above)
Index in the error_description list for "phi"
Index in the error_description list for "r"
Index in the error_description list for "z"
Name or description of every element
Position of the start point of every element
Toroidal angle (oriented counter-clockwise when viewing from above)
Index in the error_description list for "phi"
Index in the error_description list for "r"
Index in the error_description list for "z"
Type of every element: 1: line segment, its ends are given by the start and end points; index = 2: arc of a circle; index = 3: full circle
Index in the error_description list for "resistance"
Index in the error_description list for "data"

coils_non_axisymmetric.coil[:].current.documentation: Current in one turn of the coil (to be multiplied by the number of turns to calculate the magnetic field generated). Sign convention : a positive current generates a positive radial magnetic field

coils_non_axisymmetric.coil[:].current.d.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "data"

coils_non_axisymmetric.coil[:].resistanc.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "resistance"

coils_non_axisymmetric.coil[:].turns.documentation: Number of total turns in the coil. May be a fraction when describing the coil connections.

coils_non_axisymmetric.coil[:].turns_err.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "turns"

coils_non_axisymmetric.coil[:].voltage.documentation: Voltage on the coil terminals. Sign convention : a positive power supply voltage (and power supply current) generates a positive radial magnetic field

coils_non_axisymmetric.coil[:].voltage.d.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "data"

coils_non_axisymmetric.ids_properties.documentation: Interface Data Structure properties. This element identifies the node above as an IDS

coils_non_axisymmetric.ids_properties.co.documentation: Any comment describing the content of this IDS

coils_non_axisymmetric.ids_properties.cr.documentation: Date at which this data has been produced

coils_non_axisymmetric.ids_properties.ho.documentation: This node must be filled (with 0, 1, or 2) for the IDS to be valid. If 1, the time of this IDS is homogeneous, i.e. the time values for this IDS are stored in the time node just below the root of this IDS. If 0, the time values are stored in the various time fields at lower levels in the tree. In the case only constant or static nodes are filled within the IDS, homogeneous_time must be set to 2

coils_non_axisymmetric.ids_properties.oc.description: occurrence number [NOTE: this field only exists in OMAS and is not part of the ITER PDM]

coils_non_axisymmetric.ids_properties.pl.documentation: Information about the plugins used to write/read this IDS. This structure is filled automatically by the Access Layer at GET/PUT time, no need to fill it via a user program.
Plugin infrastructure used to GET the data
Plugin infrastructure used to PUT the data
Set of IDS nodes for which a plugin has been applied

Plugins actually used to read back a node (potentially, multiple plugins can be applied, listed in reverse order of application). This information is filled by the plugin infrastructure during the GET operation.
List of the code specific parameters in XML format
Path of the node within the IDS, following the syntax given in the link below. If empty, means the plugin applies to the whole IDS.
Plugins used to PUT a node (potentially, multiple plugins can be applied, if so they are listed by order of application)
List of the code specific parameters in XML format
Plugins to be used to read back a node (potentially, multiple plugins can be applied, listed in reverse order of application)
List of the code specific parameters in XML format

coils_non_axisymmetric.ids_properties.pr.documentation: Set of IDS nodes for which the provenance is given. The provenance information applies to the whole structure below the IDS node. For documenting provenance information for the whole IDS, set the size of this array of structure to 1 and leave the child "path" node empty
Path of the node within the IDS, following the syntax given in the link below. If empty, means the provenance information applies to the whole IDS.

List of sources used to import or calculate this node, identified as explained below. In case the node is the result of of a calculation / data processing, the source is an input to the process described in the "code" structure at the root of the IDS. The source can be an IDS (identified by a URI or a persitent identifier, see syntax in the link below) or non-IDS data imported directly from an non-IMAS database (identified by the command used to import the source, or the persistent identifier of the data source). Often data are obtained by a chain of processes, however only the last process input are recorded here. The full chain of provenance has then to be reconstructed recursively from the provenance information contained in the data sources.
Name of the person in charge of producing this data

coils_non_axisymmetric.ids_properties.so.documentation: Source of the data (any comment describing the origin of the data : code, path to diagnostic signals, processing method, ...). Superseeded by the new provenance structure.

coils_non_axisymmetric.ids_properties.ve.documentation: Version of the access layer package used to PUT this IDS
Version of Access Layer used to PUT this IDS
Programming language of the Access Layer high level API used to PUT this IDS
Version of Data Dictionary used to PUT this IDS

coils_non_axisymmetric.latency.documentation: Upper bound of the delay between input command received from the RT network and actuator starting to react. Applies globally to the system described by this IDS unless specific latencies (e.g. channel-specific or antenna-specific) are provided at a deeper level in the IDS structure.

coils_non_axisymmetric.latency_error_ind.documentation: Index in the error_description list for "latency"
